    "name": "Marsquake",
    "profile": "The end of 2020 marked the official beginning of the band Marsquake, founded by Gabi Neagu and Ștefan Maidaniuc, who laid the groundwork for the project and set its artistic direction. The band's style is alternative rock with diverse influences from the rock sphere and beyond. Their released compositions feature elements of nu-metal, stoner, industrial, grunge, progressive, and new-wave.\r\n\r\nAdi Scrab joined the band in 2022, significantly shaping their sound by adding industrial, symphonic, and experimental accents through masterfully handled keyboards.\r\n\r\nThe band's debut took place at the \"Constelații Rock 2023\" festival in Râmnicu Vâlcea, where they enjoyed public success. This was followed by a series of concerts in Bucharest and across the country, with the year's end marking a lineup change.\r\n\r\nThe year 2024 represents a new beginning for the band, with the lineup solidified by George Bambu and Alexandru Vasilescu.\r\n\r\nGeorge Bambu, an enthusiast of Romanian rock, enhances the rh",
